10... f5 11. Qh5 Qf6 12. f4
{ White is well-advised to play this move to try to keep Blacks center pawns under control. }
12... Bd6
{ Black decides to castle kingside. The other approach   12...Bd7  13.Nd2  O-O-O  was good as well. }
13. Nd2 O-O 14. Rae1 Bd7 15. a3 a6 16. Kh1 Rac8 17. Nb3 Rc7
{ An interesting move; the rook can defend on the seventh rank, but it can also swing over to the attack as we will see soon ! It is obvious that Whites attacking attempts did not lead to much and Blacks extra pawn gives him an advantage. }
18. Nxg6
{ A risky exchange from a strategic point of view, as Black now gets even more influence in the center as a result of a potential ...g6-g5 break. }
18... hxg6 19. Qf3 Bc8 20. Rd1 Rh7 21. Be2 Qh8 22. h3 g5
{ Very typical. Without Whites f4-pawn, Blacks center pawns will become a deadly force. }
