s, while Whites queenside structure is weak.  14.Rxc3   14.Qxf3  Qxd4+  15.Be3  Qd5  -+   14.Kxf3  Qc6+  15.Kf2  Qd6  ∓  14...Bxd1  15.Rxd1  O-O !?  16.Rxc7  Nd5  ∓  White can also transpose to the quite theoretical, but dubious Winckelmann-Reimer-Gambit with   5.a3  Bxc3+  6.bxc3  This option will be discussed in the next game. }
